    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD model accuracy within 7% of measured NIH across five nominal operating points (2–5 L/min, 3500–4000 RPM), with RH < 1.0 at all points. The assessment team notes that high-shear impeller tip regions and near-stall low-flow conditions (below 2.0 L/min) identified in the COU are addressed in a parallel characterization effort; those results are to be incorporated in a subsequent credibility assessment update prior to final regulatory submission. On the basis of the current evidence package, the model is accepted for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions within the validated operating envelope.",
